==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pendent
<hw>Pend"ent</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧nd"⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pendens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>pendere</ets> to
hang, to be suspended. Cf. <er>Pendant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Supported from above; suspended; depending; pendulous; hanging;
<as>as, a <ex>pendent</ex> leaf</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>pendent</xex> world.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Often their tresses, when shaken, with <qex>pendent</qex> icicles
tinkle.</q> <rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Jutting over; projecting; overhanging.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A vapor sometime like a . . . <xex>pendent</xex> rock.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pendentive</ent>⟦br⟧
